          "description": "The self-check claims the out-of-scope lines literally match the contract strings, but they do not. The markdown splits `Code implementation or execution` into two bullets and rewrites the workflow/runtime bullets, so the stated self-check result cannot be true.",
          "source_section": "Self-check; Contract summary.out_of_scope; <scope>; <steps> step 3"
        }
      ],
      "redesign_guidance": "Pick one authoritative representation for the contract and regenerate the markdown and self-check from it. In particular, decide whether `package_files` stores full canonical paths or only filenames, make that choice consistent everywhere, and align the `<scope>` strings exactly with the contract if literal matching is required."
    },
    {
      "id": "group-2",
      "summary": "The governed review process described in the contract intent/governance is not fully specified in the operational steps, leaving material review-state semantics undefined.",
      "severity": "major",
      "findings": [
        {
          "id": "f3",
          "severity": "major",
          "description": "The contract intent explicitly calls out an improved review process with split-verdict and arbitration, and governance enables `allow_single_arbitration_round = true`, but the role markdown never defines when arbitration occurs, whether it consumes one of the three review rounds, what artifacts record it, or how it affects freeze eligibility.",
          "source_section": "Contract summary.intent; Contract summary.governance; <inputs>; <guardrails>; <steps> step 4; <completion>"
        },
        {
          "id": "f4",
          "severity": "major",
          "description": "The freeze predicate is defined only as `all reviewer verdicts are approved` plus no blocking/major issues from the leader, which leaves no explicit lifecycle path for the split-verdict/arbitration behavior the contract says this tool now supports.",
          "source_section": "<guardrails>; <steps> step 4; Contract summary.intent; Contract summary.governance"
        }
      ],
      "redesign_guidance": "Add explicit arbitration and split-verdict semantics to the role package: trigger conditions, round accounting relative to `max_review_rounds = 3`, artifact outputs, and the exact mapping from mixed verdicts to `frozen`, `blocked`, `pushback`, or `resume_required`."
    }
  ],
  "residual_risks": [
    "Decision-history preservation across `update` and `fix` is stated as a guardrail but still lacks a concrete merge/appending rule, which may cause inconsistent canonical decision logs after the blocking issues are fixed.",
    "Terminal artifact content requirements such as participant records, provenance, unresolved issues, and validation evidence are named, but the package does not yet lock their schema or placement, so downstream validation may still drift."
  ],
  "strengths": [
    "Authority boundaries are mostly disciplined: the draft clearly subordinates itself to the COO-controlled runtime contract and treats project docs as reference evidence only.",
    "Canonical artifacts versus run-scoped evidence are separated cleanly, and non-frozen runs are explicitly prevented from overwriting canonical files.",
    "The step structure is operationally clear and covers validation, draft generation, self-check, review loop, and terminal resolution in a sensible order."
  ]
}

